OL,3,CFuneral of Moya Brennan filled with
OL,4,CLoud applause, cheers and standing
OL,5,Covation
OL,7,FMoya Brennan has been remembered as
OL,8,Fthe "First Lady of Celtic music" at
OL,9,Fher funeral in Co Donegal.
OL,11,FThe musician and songwriter, who
OL,12,Fplayed the harp with the Grammy award-
OL,13,Fwinning Celtic fusion pioneers
OL,14,FClannad, died peacefully at the age of
OL,15,F73 earlier this week.
OL,17,FThe band ` siblings Ciaran, Pol and
OL,18,FMoya Brennan and their twin uncles
OL,19,FNoel and Padraig Duggan ` achieved
OL,20,Fhuge international success over their
OL,21,F40-year career.
OL,26,@pD@EOUpD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
