PN,44806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776697866
OL,3,CFuneral of Moya Brennan filled with
OL,4,CLoud applause, cheers and standing
OL,5,Covation
OL,7,FHe told those gathered music stood
OL,8,Fstill, and Brennan's "beautiful harp
OL,9,Fstood silently in the corner of her
OL,10,Froom, as though keeping its own quiet
OL,11,Fvigil of respect and honour".
OL,13,FBut he said in the hours and days that
OL,14,Ffollowed, her home "became again a
OL,15,Fplace of friendship and love, of
OL,16,Fkindness and light, a centre of song
OL,17,Fand deep spirituality, where tears of
OL,18,Fsadness and tears of joy mingled with
OL,19,Fmemories so lovingly shared by young
OL,20,Fand old alike".
OL,26,@pD@VOUsD@\O]vD@TOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776697866
OL,3,CFuneral of Moya Brennan filled with
OL,4,CLoud applause, cheers and standing
OL,5,Covation
OL,7,FHe said: "In these past few days,
OL,8,Fgrace and grief stood side by side,
OL,9,Fembraced and danced to the beautiful
OL,10,Fmusic as memories were shared through
OL,11,Ftears of sadness and sorrow and tears
OL,12,Fof joy and gratitude."
OL,14,FFr O Fearraig continued his tribute in
OL,15,Fboth the Irish language and English,
OL,16,Fdescribing Brennan as "above all, a
OL,17,Fwoman of music and melody, a woman of
OL,18,Fmotherhood, and mission".
OL,26,@oD@JOUtD@VO]xD@WOUzD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776697866
OL,3,CFuneral of Moya Brennan filled with
OL,4,CLoud applause, cheers and standing
OL,5,Covation
OL,7,FHe added: "She knew that her gift was
OL,8,Ffrom God, and she used that gift
OL,9,Ffaithfully and well, allowing her
OL,10,Fvoice and harp to harmonise and become
OL,11,Finstruments of beauty, peace, and
OL,12,Fblessing for the world.
OL,14,F"It has been said that, through her
OL,15,Fvoice and her gifted playing of the
OL,16,Fharp, Maire carried the rugged beauty,
OL,17,Fthat quiet strength, the ancient
OL,18,Ftimeless mystery, and rich soul of
OL,19,FDonegal to audiences right across the
OL,20,Fworld."
OL,26,@oD@KOUvD@AOU|D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776697866
OL,3,CFuneral of Moya Brennan filled with
OL,4,CLoud applause, cheers and standing
OL,5,Covation
OL,7,FThe priest quoted her fellow musician
OL,8,Fand friend Mairead Ni Mhaonaigh: "She
OL,9,Fmay be gone, but the voice will
OL,10,Fremain."
OL,12,FHe added: "Through her singing and
OL,13,Fharp-playing, she gave expression not
OL,14,Fonly to melody, but to the deep
OL,15,Fspirit, beauty, and soul of her people
OL,16,Fand place."
OL,18,FThe funeral finished with loud
OL,19,Fapplause, cheers and a standing
OL,20,Fovation.
OL,26,@pD@bOUrD@HO]tD@KOUxD@KO]
